Scanner is a type of java utility, and it helps analyze a number that the user inputs
There are steps to writing programs, and the first one is to understand what the program's purpose is
The next step is to forget about actually writing the code, and just mentally picture what the logical steps towards getting the program finished are
After that, start writing the syntax. This helps make sure the code's basic backbone will be in place, and that it will work properly
% will get the remainder of two numbers after they are divided
In eclipse, Ctrl+Shift+F formats the code to how it should be, which allows the user to have a simpler way of finding mistakes
